In this op-ed, President Obama reflects on the 10th anniversary of the 9/11 attacks. He emphasizes the need to honor the victims by keeping the country strong and true to their memory. He discusses how he and his family talked to their daughters about the attacks and highlights the unity and resilience that emerged in the aftermath. President Obama acknowledges the challenges the country has faced in the last decade but also emphasizes the strength and resilience of the United States. He calls for a National Day of Service and Remembrance and encourages Americans to serve their communities. Finally, he urges the country to regain the sense of common purpose and unity that emerged after 9/11, emphasizing that when Americans choose to move forward together, the United States can emerge stronger than before.